nodes.text: A male individual was the captain of 1729, a supply ship for the Desolation Alley prison on Oovo IV. His co-pilot noticed an anomaly in the starship's sensor wake which the captain assumed would be a glitch, as the sensors of 1729 had malfunctioned before. After checking again, the co-pilot agreed that it was a glitch, but the anomaly was actually bounty hunter Jango Fett using 1729 to slip his ship past the shields surrounding Desolation Alley.
1729's captain's only appearance has been in a cutscene in the 2002 video game, Star Wars: Bounty Hunter, in which he was voiced by Mel Fair.
